5:
Excellent, sales are on the rise. I'm
glad to see everything is moving
along smoothly even when I'm not
here.
8:
No other trouble to report on? Both
caravan-related or otherwise.
11:
Nothing in particular. With you away,
we're all busy managing the
caravan.
12:
I think we've managed to instill a
sense of responsibility in members
across all locations as a result.
14:
Got it. I'm glad to hear that. Keep up
the good work—I'm counting on you.
17:
This is a brand new product of
mine—a precious pearl, a type of
stone only birthed in a place
blessed with water.
19:
Show this to a collector, and you'll
find yourself swimming in more
money than you know what to do
with.
23:
Getting this whole operation to run
effectively without you was really a
smart move, Tahweel. You're a
genius!
27:
No, Alk, it's precisely the
opposite—any organization that
can't run without its leader is
doomed to fail.
30:
Some degree of faith and trust in
your subordinates is absolutely
necessary.
34:
Sounds like you just want less work
to do.
38:
How rude! I'll have you know that I've
got plenty on my plate—starting
now, in fact.
41:
Ah, that's right. Almost forgot to
mention this—I'll be having you
accompany me.
44:
Welcome, Mr. Tahweel. What brings
you to us today?
46:
A business proposal. I'd like to set up
a shop in your very town.
49:
Making this town more easily
accessible would prove lucrative for
future trade. What do you say?
52:
Of course! Please feel free to do so!
We have many young people who
would be willing to help out!
56:
Glad to hear it. Once you gather
whoever you can, my man here will
fill you in on the details.
64:
That look in your eye suggests
suspicion, dear Nimbus. Do you
doubt me?
67:
This place is pretty much the
definition of the boonies. What
exactly is lucrative about it?
70:
An opportunity to expand into a
developing market, is what.
73:
Once we get established here, we'll
be the only game in town—a
monopoly in the making.
77:
Setting up here isn't exactly free
though, is it?
80:
It's an investment. All it has to do is
yield profit eventually—this is a
long-term strategy.
86:
Um, are you really sure we should
go with you? We don't want to fan
the flames any further...
90:
Nonsense, you're just perfect for the
job. I need bodyguards, and you
know the situation better than
anyone.
95:
We're not your manservants, you
know.
100:
Oh, just a check-in, is all. I wanted to
see if you've repented since our last
meeting.
103:
Come on, now. That was a joke. You
don't want to make your superiors
any angrier, do you?
106:
If you don't have anything to say,
then leave. Just looking at your face
makes me sick.
108:
Quite a temper on you... As a matter
of fact, I do have something to say.
111:
As long as you don't go acting the
way you did before, I'd be willing to
partner up with you. What do you
say?
116:
Well, to be totally honest, I was
hoping to use this as an opportunity
to rein you in.
118:
If you pull the same stunt as before,
I'll wipe you out.
122:
But of course, having to do that
would mean incurring serious
losses. I'd prefer a more... profitable
approach.
128:
Now that's what I'm talking about!
Don't worry, I'll make sure that you
benefit from this arrangement too!
131:
I look forward to your continued
patronage.
141:
What, are you looking for a drinking
buddy?
145:
Alk's not old enough to partake, 
so... I guess I am.
150:
You know, you're really different now,
after all that stuff happened.
153:
Different? I wouldn't say so. I'm just
doing business as I always have.
156:
I suppose I have changed my
perspective slightly though. 
I stopped looking at everything in
terms of profits and losses, for one.
159:
And... I guess I decided that being
true to myself was a better look.
161:
Still, you won't see me baring my
heart open for everyone to hear.
That's just my personality—and
yours too, I think.
164:
Hah. Don't go lumping us together
like that.
168:
I still haven't given up on recruiting
you into my caravan, you know.
170:
I'm expecting a promising
development on that front in the
future—don't let me down.
173:
Sorry, but I'm not interested. Your
caravan's food sucks.
176:
But I guess I can help you out from
time to time. You've got a promise to
keep, after all.
179:
That I do.
In my own way, I'll see that promise
realized.
